.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "August 2023" "Version 1.0"

.SH NAME
simple_shell - A basic command-line shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include\ "main.h"

.B Interactive Mode: ./hsh

.B Non-Interactive Mode: [COMMAND]... | ./hsh
.P


.SH DESCRIPTION
The simple_shell is a simple command-line prompt that emulates basic functionalities of the Bash shell. It was built as a project for Holberton School San Juan. The shell allows users to execute basic commands, similar to those found in the Bash shell.

.SH COMPILATION
To compile the shell, use the following command:
.B
gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh

.SH SYNTAX
The shell processes user input commands in the following syntax:
.B
command name {arguments}
.PP
For example:
.B
ls -l: List all files and directories in long format.
.PP
cat shell.h: Display the content of the file named "shell.h".

.PP
For more information on a specific command, you can use the man command, which provides detailed documentation about that command.

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
The shell includes built-in commands:

.TP
.B
exit: Terminate the shell. Returns -1 to indicate termination.

.TP
.B
env: Display all environment variables with their values.

.TP
.B
help: Display a list of available built-in commands.


